Text: **Codex Entry - North Korea's Journal** Ah, what an utterly fascinating scenario unfolded today.
Russia, in his typically over-the-top fashion, employed me, North, to retrieve a *glowing limo*.
Sounds like the beginning of a superhero origin story I've secretly coveted, amidst my avid collection of vintage hoodwinked pop culture wonders—none of which I’ll admit to possessing, of course.
In exchange, all I asked for was a girlie magazine.
A fair trade for potential superpowers, wouldn’t you say?
I know some might think this whole scenario a bit mad—but for me, it's just another day in my quest for a Juche-style victory on my elusive adventure ride of self-relevance on the global stage.
Over a casual scoop of kimchi, I envisioned myself as a poised superhero, my cape fluttering to the dramatic tunes of my Casio keyboard symphonies.
Ukraine teasingly referred to the limo as a nightlight which only added fuel to my fascination.
Maybe if it can top McDonald's cheeseburgers in sparking joy, I shall put aside more schemes to acquire it.
Oh, these international charades are nothing if not endlessly amusing.
Maybe another fictional military parade in the backyard, to which I'm inviting—well, myself.
Can’t wait for the surprised birds to drop by!
